<p class="">I am sure that the right hon. and learned Gentleman will understand me when I say that we on this side of the House would rather reserve comment and judgment until we have a chance of studying the White Paper, which I understand will be available this afternoon. I want to put only one point, and that is on how this matter is to be handled in the Debate. If I understood aright, the Government propose to put down a Motion of their own, which will, I suppose, mean that the opening speech of the Debate will be made by a Government spokesman.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
